1.title: The Hyphenated Name Episode
1.plot: Nick and Suzanne argue about whether to keep Nick's last name or Suzanne's.

2.title: The Credit Check Episode
2.plot: Nick wants a new sports utility vehicle, but Suzanne refuses, saying that there's no room in the budget, so he goes behind her back to check his credit score. Meanwhile Nick and Kevin compete through video games.

3.title: The Day Off Episode
3.plot: Suzanne decides that she needs more time to herself, but she has nothing to do with her free time. Meanwhile, Nick introduces the kids to his mom, Marilyn.

4.title: The Soccer Episode
4.plot: Nick decides to bond with Kevin over soccer. Meanwhile Suzanne finds Lindsey's lack of face-to-face communication strange, so she creates a fake social media profile to spy on her online life.

5.title: The Rat in the House Episode
5.plot: Kevin's weird best friend, Troy, brings over a pet rat that Kevin keeps and lovingly calls 'Whitey' - unfortunately Whitey escapes into the house, and Nick is terrified of rats.

6.title: The Booty Episode
6.plot: Nick goes to a pirate-themed "sexy restaurant" without telling Suzanne. Meanwhile Lindsey and Kevin bug her about wanting more of an allowance.

7.title: The Viral Video Episode
7.plot: Suzanne dances in her underwear to a rap song in Kevin's bedroom while doing provocative poses - unaware that Kevin had been talking on a video-chat service with his friend Troy, and that the webcam was left on by mistake.

8.title: The Michele Obama Sweater Episode
8.plot: Suzanne won't allow Lindsey to order a sweater online, so Lindsey asks Nick to buy it for her instead. Meanwhile Kevin pretends to be an orphan to raise money for Martin to get a collector's baseball bat.

9.title: The No Nah Nah Episode
9.plot: Nick is reluctant to make love to Suzanne while the kids are in the house, so she assumes he is sleeping around. Meanwhile Martin tries to figure out what age his new adolescent-looking girlfriend is.

10.title: The Get Together Episode
10.plot: Nick arranges a get-together for his friends and family, but things get awkward when somebody from Suzanne's past shows up.

1.title: The Mr. Himdependent Episode
1.plot: Nick becomes the sports anchor at a local TV station. Meanwhile Suzanne's ex-husband tries to convince her that he should be able to pay less child support, and Suzanne and Gigi plan a bachelor party.

2.title: The We Ain't Going Out Like That Episode
2.plot: Nick gets bothered when, on his and Suzanne's date night, Suzanne plans every single detail without letting him decide anything. Meanwhile, Lindsey and Kevin decide to watch some VHS tapes and find a mysterious eighties sitcom.

3.title: The Oh No She Di-in't Episode
3.plot: Suzanne gets jealous of one of Nick's pretty young co-workers. Meanwhile, Gigi falls in love with a man who has children, so she hangs out with Lindsey and Kevin to help her learn how to relate to kids better.

4.title: The Nick's Manny-Pedi Episode
4.plot: Suzanne infiltrates Nick's night with the boys, so he retaliates by crashing her all-lady spa getaway.

5.title: The Gold Party Episode
5.plot: Nick suspects that Suzanne's diamond ring isn't real, so he decides to replace it on her. Elsewhere, Marilyn arranges a Cash-for-Gold party at the house.

6.title: The Boy Has Style Episode
6.plot: Lindsey has a crush on a boy in her class, but Suzanne thinks the boy is gay.

7.title: The Man and the Bragging Snafu Episode
7.plot: Nick and Suzanne consider enrolling the kids in private school, but end up confused by the whole process. Kevin gets a modeling job but only manages to mess it up.

8.title: The Suzanne Theft Auto Episode
8.plot: Suzanne gets weirdly involved in Kevin's science project, and Lindsey ends up a suspect in scratching her mom's car after using it during driving lessons.

9.title: The Despicable E Episode
9.plot: Lindsey falls for a celebrity DJ. Meanwhile, Suzanne teaches Kevin how to do laundry.

10.title: The She Got Game Night Episode
10.plot: When the Kingston-Persons decide to have a game night, all bets are off, as unlikely friends are drawn to one another when paired together for games.

11.title: The Valentine's Day Episode
11.plot: Nick tries to help out Kevin with Valentine's Day at school, only to fail miserably.

12.title: The Parent Teacher Trap Episode
12.plot: There is a problem with Suzanne and Nick when Suzanne worries about him. Meanwhile, Lindsey and Kevin try to cash in a cup for five hundred dollars.

13.title: The Whose Card Is It Anyway Episode
13.plot: Nick and Suzanne end up in front of a TV judge after Nick spends a gift card and lies about it.

14.title: The Suzanne Gets One-Upped Episode
14.plot: Nick plans a surprise honeymoon for Suzanne but isn't good at keeping it a secret.

15.title: The First .45 Episode
15.plot: Kevin finds a gun in his mom's closet and plays with it, only to get in serious trouble later on.

16.title: The Take Your Kids to Work Day Episode
16.plot: Suzanne takes Lindsey to work with her.

17.title: The Fall of Troy Episode
17.plot: Kevin's best friend, Troy, is being bullied by a kid named Jason. Surprisingly Kevin takes Jason's side, but when Troy is nearly beat-up, Kevin has to decide whether or not to stand up for him.
